---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="html">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    HTML Structure
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      Every HTML document follows a specific structure that tells browsers how to interpret and display the content. Understanding this structure is fundamental to writing proper HTML.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Basic HTML Document Structure</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My First Web Page</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph of text.</p>
</body>
</html>`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">HTML Document Components</h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-custom text-sm sm:text-base">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-custom-secondary">
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Element</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Purpose</th>
            <th class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2 text-custom-primary">Description</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="text-custom-secondary">
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2"><code>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</code></td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Document Type</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Declares HTML5 document type</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2"><code>&lt;html&gt;</code></td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Root Element</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Container for all HTML content</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2"><code>&lt;head&gt;</code></td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Document Head</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Contains metadata and page information</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2"><code>&lt;body&gt;</code></td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Document Body</td>
            <td class="border border-custom px-3 py-2 sm:px-4 sm:py-2">Contains visible page content</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Key Structural Elements</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</strong> must be the first line</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">&lt;html&gt;</strong> element wraps all content</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">&lt;head&gt;</strong> contains metadata, title, and links to CSS/JS</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">&lt;body&gt;</strong> contains all visible content</li>
        <li>Use proper indentation for better code readability</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>